# DISCUSSION 
Spatio-temporal movement patterns generally are individual and differ between societal groups due to factors such as weekly schedules or economic aspects. As students have more heterogeneity in their weekly work schedule their movement patterns reflect this inconsistency. Students more likely travel by public transport or other low cost travelling means as other societal groups, which in turn also affect their spatio-temporal movement patterns regarding our investigated environmental factors. 

In the course of this project it became clear, that the Posmo App comes with severe uncertainties and tracking errors. Quantifying those uncertainties would be subject to another semester project in itself. 


